WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.710 --> 00:00:06.710
- Previously on Siren...
- Bring it in!

2
00:00:06.711 --> 00:00:08.209
We caught something
out there.

3
00:00:08.210 --> 00:00:10.249
It attacked Chris.
He had to get airlifted out.

4
00:00:10.250 --> 00:00:12.289
Big-ass military
commando helicopter.

5
00:00:12.290 --> 00:00:13.290
You really don't know
what attacked him?

6
00:00:13.291 --> 00:00:15.289
This was a predator.

7
00:00:15.290 --> 00:00:17.499
150 years ago.

8
00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:19.959
a local fishing captain
fell in love with a mermaid

9
00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:21.329
in these very waters.

10
00:00:21.330 --> 00:00:23.249
Had a report
six weeks ago.

11
00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:25.329
Japanese fisherman
claimed he saw
a sea creature.

12
00:00:25.330 --> 00:00:27.039
We knew something
was out there.

13
00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:28.040
That's when I alerted
your people.

14
00:00:28.041 --> 00:00:29.499
You okay?

15
00:00:29.500 --> 00:00:31.040
Little girl
runnin' away from home.

16
00:00:34.880 --> 00:00:36.249
You're sick. Can I see?

17
00:00:36.250 --> 00:00:38.249
Hey.

18
00:00:38.250 --> 00:00:39.539
This is Ryn. I don't
think she speaks English.

19
00:00:42.250 --> 00:00:45.459
Your ancestors slaughtered
those beautiful creatures.

20
00:00:45.460 --> 00:00:48.289
Genocide... that's your legacy.

21
00:00:48.290 --> 00:00:49.879
Hey. we got somethin'.

22
00:00:49.880 --> 00:00:51.499
That's big.

23
00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:52.540
Look.

24
00:01:07.420 --> 00:01:08.709
Stop! Don't!

25
00:01:08.710 --> 00:01:10.249
What the hell?!

26
00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:11.959
You don't want to do that.
That could kill it.

27
00:01:11.960 --> 00:01:13.209
Thought you said
you came out here
to help us.

28
00:01:13.210 --> 00:01:16.039
I had a clean shot
till you stepped in.

29
00:01:16.040 --> 00:01:18.169
Almost like you don't
want us catching it.

30
00:01:18.170 --> 00:01:21.169
Look. if this thing really is
what you think it is.

31
00:01:21.170 --> 00:01:23.379
we need to protect it.
not kill it.

32
00:01:25.250 --> 00:01:27.829
We want what belongs to us.

33
00:01:27.830 --> 00:01:29.579
and we want
to get Chris back.

34
00:01:29.580 --> 00:01:31.379
If you don't want
the same thing.

35
00:01:31.380 --> 00:01:32.959
I don't know what the hell
you're doing on the boat.

36
00:01:34.380 --> 00:01:35.669
Hear that?

37
00:01:40.170 --> 00:01:43.329
It's like. I don't know.
it's injured?

38
00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:48.250
Maybe I hit it.

39
00:01:51.420 --> 00:01:52.749
It's underneath.

40
00:01:52.750 --> 00:01:54.119
It's underneath the boat!

41
00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:55.330
We gotta get it.

42
00:01:57.580 --> 00:01:58.960
Ben!

43
00:02:00.210 --> 00:02:01.289
- Ben!
- Ben!

44
00:02:09.170 --> 00:02:10.210
- Ben!
- Ben!

45
00:02:32.620 --> 00:02:33.620
Come on!

46
00:02:35.120 --> 00:02:36.210
Ben!

47
00:02:37.420 --> 00:02:39.460
- What the...
- What the hell is that?

48
00:02:40.620 --> 00:02:42.419
Ben! Ben. come on!

49
00:02:42.420 --> 00:02:44.040
Get over here.

50
00:03:29.620 --> 00:03:31.749
It might be
a Doppler current profiler.

51
00:03:31.750 --> 00:03:34.669
Oceanographers uses them
to study current patterns.

52
00:03:34.670 --> 00:03:35.959
When we had the creature
in the hold.

53
00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:38.119
it... it made a sound.

54
00:03:38.120 --> 00:03:40.289
not too different
from the sound this thing makes.

55
00:03:40.290 --> 00:03:42.459
Right.

56
00:03:42.460 --> 00:03:46.919
Well. there's a lot
of scientific monitoring
devices floating out there.

57
00:03:46.920 --> 00:03:48.119
Could be a lot of things.

58
00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:49.459
Well. just think about it.

59
00:03:49.460 --> 00:03:51.289
We were out here. what.
like. a few days ago?

60
00:03:51.290 --> 00:03:52.379
And this thing wasn't here.

61
00:03:52.380 --> 00:03:53.419
And then we catch
that creature.

62
00:03:53.420 --> 00:03:55.039
and. all of a sudden.
it just appears?

63
00:03:55.040 --> 00:03:56.459
Somebody put it here.
It's gotta be connected.

64
00:03:56.460 --> 00:03:58.330
Yeah. you could be right.

65
00:04:03.540 --> 00:04:05.379
You know. that was...

66
00:04:05.380 --> 00:04:06.579
That was a pretty sick thing
you did back there.

67
00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:08.379
diving in like that.

68
00:04:08.380 --> 00:04:11.209
Yeah. Well. it seemed
like a good idea at the time.

69
00:04:11.210 --> 00:04:14.419
Look. I'm sorry.

70
00:04:14.420 --> 00:04:16.419
okay. if I pissed you off
earlier.

71
00:04:16.420 --> 00:04:18.709
I just feel differently
about it than you guys.

72
00:04:18.710 --> 00:04:21.290
It doesn't mean that I
don't want to find Chris.

73
00:04:22.420 --> 00:04:24.539
I appreciate it.

74
00:04:24.540 --> 00:04:26.459
For real.

75
00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:28.209
Couldn't tell.

76
00:04:28.210 --> 00:04:29.420
'cause you were being
such a dick about it.

77
00:04:34.710 --> 00:04:35.960
What is it?

78
00:04:37.710 --> 00:04:41.329
I don't know.
This thing looks
like a camera.

79
00:04:41.330 --> 00:04:43.789
There's probably some kind
of tracking device on it. too.

80
00:04:43.790 --> 00:04:45.249
We should try to disable it.

81
00:04:45.250 --> 00:04:46.999
I say we just power it up
and set it off.

82
00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.119
Let the military come.
They'll lead us to Chris.

83
00:04:49.120 --> 00:04:50.499
and maybe they got
the mermaid. too.

84
00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:51.290
I wouldn't.

85
00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:54.579
You saw what happened
the last time they came.

86
00:04:54.580 --> 00:04:56.749
We could all end up
like Chris.

87
00:04:56.750 --> 00:04:59.379
We just need to take our time

88
00:04:59.380 --> 00:05:02.420
and try to figure out
what this thing really is.

89
00:05:03.500 --> 00:05:05.580
Okay.

90
00:05:38.210 --> 00:05:39.380
Take your sister
inside the house!

91
00:06:01.880 --> 00:06:04.249
Hey! What the hell
are you doin'?

92
00:06:04.250 --> 00:06:06.709
Takin' my clothes?

93
00:06:06.710 --> 00:06:08.879
I am sick of you little junkies
comin' around here

94
00:06:08.880 --> 00:06:09.960
messin' with my stuff.

95
00:06:11.330 --> 00:06:13.670
Don't you threaten me.

96
00:07:07.670 --> 00:07:09.959
Hey. it's Ben.
Leave me a message.

97
00:07:11.170 --> 00:07:12.879
Hey. it's me.

98
00:07:12.880 --> 00:07:14.539
I'm getting worried
about you.

99
00:07:14.540 --> 00:07:17.709
Give me a call.
Let me know you're okay.

100
00:07:37.620 --> 00:07:40.619
Hello?

101
00:07:54.290 --> 00:07:56.079
You get a hold of CSI?

102
00:07:56.080 --> 00:07:58.790
Comin' from Port Angeles.
Should be here soon.

103
00:08:01.540 --> 00:08:03.459
What do you got. Clarence?

104
00:08:03.460 --> 00:08:05.249
That is Donnie Price.

105
00:08:05.250 --> 00:08:06.789
He's got some priors.

106
00:08:06.790 --> 00:08:09.749
Aggravated assault.
drunk and disorderly.

107
00:08:09.750 --> 00:08:11.419
Pants are ridin'
a little low.

108
00:08:11.420 --> 00:08:13.289
Possible sexual assault?

109
00:08:13.290 --> 00:08:15.579
Looks like he got
what he deserved.

110
00:08:15.580 --> 00:08:18.459
Or there was a third person
in the car with them.

111
00:08:18.460 --> 00:08:20.500
Somebody came up on them.

112
00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:27.419
Whoever did this was
of substantial size
and strength.

113
00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:28.540
Start lookin' around.

114
00:09:12.290 --> 00:09:14.039
How much for this?

115
00:09:14.040 --> 00:09:17.669
I'm. very sorry.
Shop's closed.

116
00:09:17.670 --> 00:09:19.209
Come back
another day?

117
00:09:19.210 --> 00:09:20.919
Thank you.

118
00:09:34.670 --> 00:09:36.290
You came back.

119
00:09:42.960 --> 00:09:44.670
Why are you here?

120
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:21.170
I...

121
00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:27.330
See?

122
00:10:38.500 --> 00:10:39.620
Look?

123
00:10:41.460 --> 00:10:42.790
You look.

124
00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:49.920
Ryn.

125
00:10:51.080 --> 00:10:52.749
Ryn.

126
00:10:52.750 --> 00:10:54.170
That's you.

127
00:11:03.960 --> 00:11:05.000
Look.

128
00:11:08.290 --> 00:11:10.620
There's another one?

129
00:11:16.920 --> 00:11:18.879
30 ccs of spinal fluid.

130
00:11:18.880 --> 00:11:22.119
and take tissue core samples
from the upper thoracic region.

131
00:11:22.120 --> 00:11:23.750
How many?

132
00:11:24.790 --> 00:11:26.959
Take six for now.

133
00:11:26.960 --> 00:11:27.960
I'll order more as needed.

134
00:11:27.961 --> 00:11:29.329
How are the other tests going?

135
00:11:29.330 --> 00:11:30.379
Very well.

136
00:11:30.380 --> 00:11:31.380
We're ready for extraction?

137
00:12:11.170 --> 00:12:12.579
I got your text.

138
00:12:12.580 --> 00:12:15.420
Where the hell
have you been?

139
00:12:17.290 --> 00:12:18.790
What's wrong?

140
00:12:26.500 --> 00:12:28.499
What happened? Are you okay?

141
00:12:28.500 --> 00:12:31.459
It's not
what you're thinking.

142
00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:33.829
How do you know
what I'm thinking?

143
00:12:33.830 --> 00:12:37.419
'Cause it literally
couldn't be anything
that you're thinking.

144
00:12:37.420 --> 00:12:39.959
I gotta show you something.

145
00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:46.670
- Yo. man.
- Yo.

146
00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:51.379
What is that?

147
00:12:51.380 --> 00:12:52.959
We found it
out in the water.

148
00:12:52.960 --> 00:12:54.579
It was making this...

149
00:12:54.580 --> 00:12:56.459
I don't know.
this weird-ass sound.

150
00:12:56.460 --> 00:12:58.879
Ben said we should
take our time.

151
00:12:58.880 --> 00:12:59.919
try to figure out
who's runnin' it.

152
00:12:59.920 --> 00:13:00.999
what they're up to.

153
00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:02.669
Wait.
Ben knows about this?

154
00:13:02.670 --> 00:13:03.999
Yeah. he came out with us.

155
00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:05.749
And now he's
telling us what to do?

156
00:13:05.750 --> 00:13:07.709
Don't trust him. man.

157
00:13:07.710 --> 00:13:09.249
The guy crewed up with us
for a few seasons.

158
00:13:09.250 --> 00:13:10.879
but he was always
just slumming it until college.

159
00:13:10.880 --> 00:13:12.209
- You know that. right?
- Yeah. but. I mean.

160
00:13:12.210 --> 00:13:13.709
you guys were
never close. all right?

161
00:13:13.710 --> 00:13:15.329
I been
through a lot with him.

162
00:13:15.330 --> 00:13:17.079
I hear you.
but look at his family.

163
00:13:17.080 --> 00:13:19.829
He's not one of us. man.

164
00:13:19.830 --> 00:13:21.250
Never has been.

165
00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:34.830
It has to be here.

166
00:13:38.960 --> 00:13:40.249
All I see
are sea lions.

167
00:13:40.250 --> 00:13:41.459
It'll be here.

168
00:13:41.460 --> 00:13:42.919
There!

169
00:13:42.920 --> 00:13:44.080
Look.

170
00:13:52.670 --> 00:13:55.499
I went in to save her.

171
00:13:55.500 --> 00:13:56.919
And then she turned
into that

172
00:13:56.920 --> 00:13:58.709
and attacked me.

173
00:13:58.710 --> 00:14:00.039
Maddie?

174
00:14:00.040 --> 00:14:01.040
Play it again.

175
00:14:01.041 --> 00:14:03.829
Okay.

176
00:14:03.830 --> 00:14:05.330
Here's a different camera.

177
00:14:11.920 --> 00:14:14.119
Man.

178
00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:16.169
This is real.

179
00:14:16.170 --> 00:14:19.709
Maddie.
this is really happening.

180
00:14:19.710 --> 00:14:21.919
I'm sorry
I didn't believe you.

181
00:14:21.920 --> 00:14:24.169
It's kinda hard
to believe someone

182
00:14:24.170 --> 00:14:25.499
when they tell you
they just saw...

183
00:14:25.500 --> 00:14:26.999
Mermaid.

184
00:14:27.000 --> 00:14:28.830
Yeah.

185
00:14:49.790 --> 00:14:50.790
Okay. I got...

186
00:14:53.960 --> 00:14:56.079
It's me.

187
00:14:56.080 --> 00:14:57.619
Helen.

188
00:14:57.620 --> 00:14:59.040
Helen.

189
00:15:02.920 --> 00:15:04.460
Helen.

190
00:15:07.580 --> 00:15:10.789
Hello. Helen.

191
00:15:10.790 --> 00:15:13.459
You learn quickly.

192
00:15:15.460 --> 00:15:18.669
Thank you. Lord...

193
00:15:18.670 --> 00:15:20.170
That's my neighbor's book.

194
00:15:23.330 --> 00:15:25.000
Two girls.

195
00:15:31.040 --> 00:15:32.620
"Sister."

196
00:15:35.170 --> 00:15:36.830
Sisters.

197
00:15:40.120 --> 00:15:42.579
Is that who
you're looking for?

198
00:15:42.580 --> 00:15:44.500
For your sister?

199
00:15:46.250 --> 00:15:47.620
Sister.

200
00:15:50.120 --> 00:15:51.500
I'll be damned.

201
00:15:54.210 --> 00:15:56.380
I have these for you.

202
00:15:58.170 --> 00:15:59.380
Put them on.

203
00:16:14.250 --> 00:16:16.250
Lovely.

204
00:16:24.250 --> 00:16:25.579
You need food.

205
00:16:25.580 --> 00:16:28.920
Humans love to eat.

206
00:16:30.750 --> 00:16:32.249
We do most
of our hunting

207
00:16:32.250 --> 00:16:34.040
in a supermarket.

208
00:16:42.920 --> 00:16:45.120
No. No.!

209
00:16:47.250 --> 00:16:50.119
Please. give.

210
00:16:50.120 --> 00:16:51.669
Give.

211
00:16:51.670 --> 00:16:53.169
Thank you.

212
00:16:53.170 --> 00:16:55.079
I think I know
what you need.

213
00:16:55.080 --> 00:16:58.169
You stay here.

214
00:16:58.170 --> 00:17:00.289
I'll go get you food.

215
00:17:00.290 --> 00:17:03.119
Then we'll look
for your sister.

216
00:17:03.120 --> 00:17:04.419
Okay?

217
00:17:22.120 --> 00:17:25.039
There's
something else. Maddie.

218
00:17:25.040 --> 00:17:26.579
When I went out with Xander.

219
00:17:26.580 --> 00:17:29.169
we found this device
in the water.

220
00:17:29.170 --> 00:17:32.539
Some kind of
military tracking device.

221
00:17:32.540 --> 00:17:34.749
I think
they're looking for her.

222
00:17:34.750 --> 00:17:37.209
The military?
This is crazy.

223
00:17:37.210 --> 00:17:39.999
Does anyone else
know about her?

224
00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:43.289
Yeah. just the guys
on the boat

225
00:17:43.290 --> 00:17:45.119
and Miss Hawkins.

226
00:17:45.120 --> 00:17:46.289
Helen Hawkins?

227
00:17:46.290 --> 00:17:48.579
You told her?
Why would you do that?

228
00:17:48.580 --> 00:17:50.999
She was talking
to that girl on the street.

229
00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:53.789
I... It looked like she knew
something about her.

230
00:17:53.790 --> 00:17:54.919
so I went to talk to her.

231
00:17:54.920 --> 00:17:56.379
Well. what did she say?

232
00:17:56.380 --> 00:17:57.789
She started talking
about my family. Maddie.

233
00:17:57.790 --> 00:18:00.329
She was saying I should
ask my dad about it.

234
00:18:00.330 --> 00:18:01.539
Your dad?

235
00:18:01.540 --> 00:18:04.669
Well. did you talk to him?

236
00:18:04.670 --> 00:18:06.829
Not yet.

237
00:18:06.830 --> 00:18:08.289
It's done.

238
00:18:08.290 --> 00:18:10.329
All the video's
downloaded.

239
00:18:10.330 --> 00:18:14.249
This thing.
it attacked you.

240
00:18:14.250 --> 00:18:16.249
it... it got Chris.

241
00:18:16.250 --> 00:18:18.289
It's dangerous.

242
00:18:18.290 --> 00:18:21.249
If we're
gonna go after it.
try to track it down.

243
00:18:21.250 --> 00:18:22.250
we need to be careful.

244
00:18:24.290 --> 00:18:25.170
You're right.

245
00:18:29.580 --> 00:18:32.709
Dude. you know what?
You were right.

246
00:18:32.710 --> 00:18:34.249
It makes sense.

247
00:18:34.250 --> 00:18:35.999
We reconnect
the tracking equipment.

248
00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:37.419
we power that thing up.

249
00:18:37.420 --> 00:18:38.579
and when the military
comes. boom!

250
00:18:38.580 --> 00:18:39.789
We ambush them.

251
00:18:39.790 --> 00:18:41.039
You need to calm down.

252
00:18:41.040 --> 00:18:42.329
We are not gonna
ambush the military.

253
00:18:42.330 --> 00:18:43.879
- Calm down?
- Yeah.

254
00:18:43.880 --> 00:18:45.419
You sound just like Ben.

255
00:18:45.420 --> 00:18:47.619
Okay. look. you don't
know him like I do. all right?

256
00:18:47.620 --> 00:18:49.749
Look. I told you.
stop listening to him!

257
00:18:49.750 --> 00:18:51.249
He's got no clue
what we're dealing
with right now.

258
00:18:51.250 --> 00:18:53.459
Pretty sure he's
one of the only people

259
00:18:53.460 --> 00:18:55.419
that actually does
have a clue what we're
dealing with right now.

260
00:18:55.420 --> 00:18:57.420
so maybe you should just
give him a little faith.
all right?

261
00:19:07.170 --> 00:19:09.749
That's
a good run of sockeye.

262
00:19:09.750 --> 00:19:11.579
Enjoy it while it lasts.

263
00:19:11.580 --> 00:19:13.119
Yeah. I worry
about that. too.

264
00:19:13.120 --> 00:19:14.959
but I also worry
about people.

265
00:19:14.960 --> 00:19:17.879
And right now. I'm giving
good jobs to folks
who need them.

266
00:19:17.880 --> 00:19:19.499
I wanted to ask you
something.

267
00:19:19.500 --> 00:19:22.249
I remember
that you and Grandpa

268
00:19:22.250 --> 00:19:24.169
used to talk
about Charles Pownall.

269
00:19:24.170 --> 00:19:27.499
about what really happened
back then.

270
00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:30.289
You really come here
to ask me that?

271
00:19:30.290 --> 00:19:31.420
Yeah.

272
00:19:33.380 --> 00:19:36.120
Why the sudden interest
in the family history?

273
00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:39.959
I ran into Helen Hawkins.

274
00:19:39.960 --> 00:19:41.959
Come on.

275
00:19:41.960 --> 00:19:44.379
Dad?

276
00:19:44.380 --> 00:19:46.999
Maybe I'd show up
to more family events

277
00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:48.829
like the statue unveiling

278
00:19:48.830 --> 00:19:51.920
if you told me
the real story
about our family.

279
00:19:53.460 --> 00:19:54.920
All right.

280
00:19:56.830 --> 00:20:03.329
Look. Charles
might not have been exactly
who we make him out to be.

281
00:20:03.330 --> 00:20:04.879
I can't say for sure.

282
00:20:04.880 --> 00:20:06.289
but there might have been
some mental illness.

283
00:20:06.290 --> 00:20:08.919
maybe even schizophrenia.

284
00:20:08.920 --> 00:20:11.419
Long months at sea.
a constant stream of booze.

285
00:20:11.420 --> 00:20:15.379
and.
well. he was seeing things.

286
00:20:15.380 --> 00:20:17.289
Mermaids?

287
00:20:17.290 --> 00:20:20.789
You know this.
You did the play in school.

288
00:20:20.790 --> 00:20:22.459
That's how the town
got its folklore.

289
00:20:22.460 --> 00:20:23.999
Now. as for Helen
and her stories.

290
00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:26.330
well. we all know she's
got a vivid imagination.

291
00:20:28.460 --> 00:20:30.289
That's it?

292
00:20:30.290 --> 00:20:31.420
That's it.

293
00:20:34.880 --> 00:20:36.120
Why?

294
00:20:38.500 --> 00:20:40.620
Dad. I gotta go.

295
00:20:45.250 --> 00:20:47.829
I'll take
a pound of mussels.

296
00:20:47.830 --> 00:20:50.499
And a pound
of clams.

297
00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:53.249
Yeah. make sure
you get the big ones.

298
00:20:53.250 --> 00:20:54.579
Shrimp...
give me two dozen shrimp

299
00:20:54.580 --> 00:20:56.329
and some scallops.

300
00:20:56.330 --> 00:20:58.999
Yeah. a little bit
of that sockeye. crab.

301
00:20:59.000 --> 00:21:00.419
Actually. make that two.

302
00:21:00.420 --> 00:21:02.459
I'll take two. two crabs.
Thanks. yeah.

303
00:21:02.460 --> 00:21:04.539
No. that's a baby.
I'm gonna have
to get something else.

304
00:21:04.540 --> 00:21:07.119
That nice. big salmon
over there?

305
00:21:07.120 --> 00:21:09.209
Thank you.

306
00:21:09.210 --> 00:21:10.919
Anything else?

307
00:21:10.920 --> 00:21:13.210
Got any sardines?

308
00:21:20.000 --> 00:21:21.749
Calvin?

309
00:21:21.750 --> 00:21:23.120
Hey. Calvin!

310
00:21:24.210 --> 00:21:25.419
Yeah?

311
00:21:25.420 --> 00:21:26.959
Did you move it?

312
00:21:26.960 --> 00:21:28.419
What. the thing?
No. I didn't touch it.

313
00:21:28.420 --> 00:21:30.000
Well. it's gone.

314
00:21:32.790 --> 00:21:34.709
You see?

315
00:21:34.710 --> 00:21:36.120
See what?

316
00:21:37.960 --> 00:21:40.749
The military came
and took the mermaid.

317
00:21:40.750 --> 00:21:42.459
took Chris.

318
00:21:42.460 --> 00:21:44.420
and now they came in here
and took the thing.

319
00:21:49.170 --> 00:21:51.420
We shouldn't even be
talking in here right now.

320
00:22:25.750 --> 00:22:27.290
Where am I?

321
00:22:33.580 --> 00:22:35.420
What's happening?

322
00:22:52.790 --> 00:22:54.419
They've been
out here all this time.

323
00:22:54.420 --> 00:22:56.249
so why
are they showing up now?

324
00:22:56.250 --> 00:22:57.829
I was
thinking the same thing
when I was at my dad's.

325
00:22:57.830 --> 00:22:59.669
What do you mean?

326
00:22:59.670 --> 00:23:01.419
Something brought her
closer to the surface.
all right?

327
00:23:01.420 --> 00:23:03.789
Maybe it's the change
in the oceans. you know?

328
00:23:03.790 --> 00:23:05.919
Maybe she's looking
for a new food source.

329
00:23:05.920 --> 00:23:08.119
- Same as our sea lions.
- Right.

330
00:23:08.120 --> 00:23:09.459
Thanks to my family.

331
00:23:22.670 --> 00:23:25.249
Helen Hawkins seems to know
a lot about this stuff.

332
00:23:25.250 --> 00:23:27.499
I'm hoping
she'll have some answers.

333
00:23:27.500 --> 00:23:29.459
Well. there she is.

334
00:23:29.460 --> 00:23:30.670
The town nut job.

335
00:23:32.380 --> 00:23:33.709
Yeah.

336
00:23:33.710 --> 00:23:36.580
Maybe don't say that
in front of her.

337
00:23:42.670 --> 00:23:46.459
Shop's closed.

338
00:23:46.460 --> 00:23:47.959
Sorry to bother you.

339
00:23:47.960 --> 00:23:49.579
but I just had a few more
questions I wanted to ask you.

340
00:23:49.580 --> 00:23:52.619
You told her?

341
00:23:52.620 --> 00:23:54.829
Yeah.
We can trust her.

342
00:23:54.830 --> 00:23:57.669
It's not about trust.

343
00:23:57.670 --> 00:23:59.539
No one else can know.

344
00:23:59.540 --> 00:24:03.539
These creatures
were massacred once.

345
00:24:03.540 --> 00:24:04.789
It could happen again.

346
00:24:04.790 --> 00:24:07.119
Look. we're not
gonna tell anyone. okay?

347
00:24:07.120 --> 00:24:08.209
We want to protect them. too.

348
00:24:09.580 --> 00:24:13.580
I. told you
everything I know.

349
00:24:17.330 --> 00:24:18.579
She's gone.

350
00:24:18.580 --> 00:24:21.210
probably a hundred miles
out in the ocean by now.

351
00:24:29.540 --> 00:24:31.379
Is everything okay?

352
00:24:31.380 --> 00:24:34.169
Plumbing issues.
It's an old building.

353
00:24:34.170 --> 00:24:35.919
I have things to do.

354
00:24:35.920 --> 00:24:37.749
so if you don't mind...

355
00:24:37.750 --> 00:24:39.880
This is just gonna
take a second.

356
00:24:43.040 --> 00:24:44.879
We found this in the water.

357
00:24:44.880 --> 00:24:46.749
I was wondering if you could
tell me what this sound is.

358
00:24:57.330 --> 00:24:58.379
Turn it off.

359
00:25:16.670 --> 00:25:18.830
Turn it off now!

360
00:25:37.670 --> 00:25:39.250
Sister!

361
00:25:53.380 --> 00:25:56.119
Close it. close it!

362
00:25:58.210 --> 00:25:59.829
Sister!

363
00:25:59.830 --> 00:26:01.749
Sister!

364
00:26:01.750 --> 00:26:03.209
That sound is your sister?

365
00:26:03.210 --> 00:26:05.669
She's not in there.

366
00:26:05.670 --> 00:26:07.540
It's... It's just a recording.

367
00:26:09.830 --> 00:26:11.329
Only sound.

368
00:26:13.290 --> 00:26:14.380
Better?

369
00:26:19.710 --> 00:26:21.749
There were two of them
out there.

370
00:26:21.750 --> 00:26:23.879
Her sister's
the one who got caught.

371
00:26:26.330 --> 00:26:27.749
What?

372
00:26:52.750 --> 00:26:54.539
Are you okay?

373
00:27:01.920 --> 00:27:04.919
Look. I get it.

374
00:27:04.920 --> 00:27:08.830
You came back
to find your sister. right?

375
00:27:10.750 --> 00:27:13.290
We can help you.

376
00:27:16.710 --> 00:27:18.789
Okay.

377
00:27:18.790 --> 00:27:20.209
Yes.

378
00:27:20.210 --> 00:27:21.709
She understands.

379
00:27:21.710 --> 00:27:23.749
They're highly intelligent.

380
00:27:23.750 --> 00:27:25.670
More so than humans.

381
00:27:30.420 --> 00:27:32.169
Okay.

382
00:27:32.170 --> 00:27:35.419
Ben. her sister
could be anywhere.

383
00:27:35.420 --> 00:27:37.749
How would we find her?

384
00:27:37.750 --> 00:27:38.959
I don't know.

385
00:27:38.960 --> 00:27:41.999
We should probably
start with Xander.

386
00:27:42.000 --> 00:27:43.789
I want to hear again
what happened out there.

387
00:27:43.790 --> 00:27:45.000
Maybe there's
something I missed.

388
00:27:47.880 --> 00:27:48.960
Look.

389
00:27:52.290 --> 00:27:53.959
Wait. wait.

390
00:27:53.960 --> 00:27:55.579
Hey! She...

391
00:27:55.580 --> 00:27:57.620
She can't just go out
into the world.

392
00:27:58.750 --> 00:28:00.919
Do we have a choice?

393
00:28:00.920 --> 00:28:03.539
Bring her back later.

394
00:28:03.540 --> 00:28:05.210
She's safe with me.

395
00:28:20.790 --> 00:28:22.999
I'm sorry.

396
00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:24.830
I'm sorry we did that to you.

397
00:29:04.670 --> 00:29:06.879
So how long
did you know him?

398
00:29:06.880 --> 00:29:08.999
He moved in
about eight months ago.

399
00:29:09.921 --> 00:29:11.209
Liked to party.

400
00:29:11.210 --> 00:29:12.919
had a lot of girlfriends.

401
00:29:12.920 --> 00:29:14.329
Drugs.

402
00:29:14.330 --> 00:29:15.879
Not a bad guy.

403
00:29:15.880 --> 00:29:17.499
but not good. either.

404
00:29:17.500 --> 00:29:19.669
Well. he's
not either anymore.

405
00:29:19.670 --> 00:29:21.209
Listen. if you think
of anything else.

406
00:29:21.210 --> 00:29:22.419
give me a call.
all right?

407
00:29:22.420 --> 00:29:23.420
Sheriff?

408
00:29:23.421 --> 00:29:24.709
Boy.

409
00:29:24.710 --> 00:29:25.999
Phillip.

410
00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:27.669
Vicki.

411
00:29:27.670 --> 00:29:28.670
I have a crime to report.

412
00:29:28.671 --> 00:29:30.499
Yeah?

413
00:29:30.500 --> 00:29:32.959
This little homeless girl's been
stealing clothing off my line.

414
00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:34.379
She got my daughter's
Huskies sweatshirt.

415
00:29:34.380 --> 00:29:36.039
this morning. a T-shirt.

416
00:29:36.040 --> 00:29:38.249
I went out to confront her.

417
00:29:38.250 --> 00:29:40.499
and she threw
a damn metal pole at me.

418
00:29:40.500 --> 00:29:42.959
Almost took my head off.

419
00:29:42.960 --> 00:29:44.330
Is that right?

420
00:29:46.420 --> 00:29:47.830
What'd she look like?

421
00:30:03.040 --> 00:30:05.709
Xander? Hey. yeah. I've been
trying to get a hold of you.

422
00:30:05.710 --> 00:30:07.119
Where are you?

423
00:30:08.830 --> 00:30:09.920
He's at The Anchor.

424
00:30:35.540 --> 00:30:37.119
- No.
- No.

425
00:30:37.120 --> 00:30:38.459
No. no. no. no. no. no.

426
00:30:38.460 --> 00:30:39.709
Wait. wait.

427
00:30:39.710 --> 00:30:42.119
Too many people.

428
00:30:42.120 --> 00:30:44.290
It's not safe. Not safe.

429
00:30:45.330 --> 00:30:46.669
You stay here.

430
00:30:46.670 --> 00:30:48.210
I'll stay with her.

431
00:30:49.670 --> 00:30:51.669
We'll stay together.

432
00:30:51.670 --> 00:30:54.459
Then we'll... Then...
Then we'll look
for your sister.

433
00:30:54.460 --> 00:30:56.829
Are you sure?

434
00:30:56.830 --> 00:30:57.920
Yeah.

435
00:30:59.250 --> 00:31:00.499
Do you wanna...

436
00:31:00.500 --> 00:31:02.039
You wanna wait
outside the car?

437
00:31:02.040 --> 00:31:03.670
I'll be okay.

438
00:31:06.790 --> 00:31:09.290
All right. Be careful.

439
00:31:24.960 --> 00:31:26.380
Hi.

440
00:31:41.290 --> 00:31:42.920
Decoration.

441
00:31:44.290 --> 00:31:45.540
You like them?

442
00:32:05.580 --> 00:32:08.169
Raven feather.

443
00:32:08.170 --> 00:32:09.540
Bird.

444
00:32:11.790 --> 00:32:14.539
My dad is Haida.

445
00:32:14.540 --> 00:32:17.750
They talk about how the raven
was the maker of things.

446
00:32:20.290 --> 00:32:24.499
They say he put the sun
and moon in the sky.

447
00:32:24.500 --> 00:32:28.210
brought fresh water
and fire to the land.

448
00:32:30.080 --> 00:32:33.750
They say he found
the first people
inside a giant clamshell.

449
00:32:37.620 --> 00:32:39.619
Bird.

450
00:32:39.620 --> 00:32:41.540
It's just a story.

451
00:32:44.670 --> 00:32:46.000
Made up.

452
00:32:47.750 --> 00:32:49.959
Some things are real.

453
00:32:49.960 --> 00:32:53.079
others are just stories.

454
00:32:56.330 --> 00:32:58.380
This. real.

455
00:33:01.920 --> 00:33:03.080
This.

456
00:33:04.290 --> 00:33:05.540
Real.

457
00:33:09.830 --> 00:33:10.960
Real.

458
00:33:17.670 --> 00:33:19.119
Yes.

459
00:33:19.120 --> 00:33:21.040
You're real.

460
00:33:36.920 --> 00:33:38.499
Okay.
so Chris gets attacked.

461
00:33:38.500 --> 00:33:40.789
and your dad
calls in the evac?

462
00:33:40.790 --> 00:33:42.249
Yeah.

463
00:33:42.250 --> 00:33:43.539
The military
must have been listening.

464
00:33:43.540 --> 00:33:46.209
or CG tipped them off.
I don't know.

465
00:33:46.210 --> 00:33:48.289
Did it look like there was
someone in charge?

466
00:33:48.290 --> 00:33:49.619
Yeah.

467
00:33:49.620 --> 00:33:52.249
Okay. so what...
what did he look like?

468
00:33:52.250 --> 00:33:55.119
He was a black dude.

469
00:33:55.120 --> 00:33:57.079
Okay. anything else
about him?

470
00:33:57.080 --> 00:33:59.210
I don't know why this is
any of your damn business.

471
00:34:01.120 --> 00:34:03.249
It's like they were
waitin' for us all along.

472
00:34:03.250 --> 00:34:07.329
Like. if it's
the military. man.

473
00:34:07.330 --> 00:34:08.789
then they are watching us.

474
00:34:08.790 --> 00:34:09.919
They know stuff about us.

475
00:34:09.920 --> 00:34:10.999
Xander.

476
00:34:11.000 --> 00:34:12.919
They flew off with Chris.

477
00:34:12.920 --> 00:34:14.119
they broke into our place

478
00:34:14.120 --> 00:34:15.919
and took that device.

479
00:34:15.920 --> 00:34:18.379
They are after us. man.

480
00:34:18.380 --> 00:34:20.079
Probably bugged
our apartment. too.

481
00:34:20.080 --> 00:34:22.120
- We should do a sweep.
- Yeah. Yes. definitely.

482
00:34:24.250 --> 00:34:27.169
Maybe... maybe...
Maybe we...

483
00:34:27.170 --> 00:34:30.499
Maybe we post that footage
from the deck. yeah?

484
00:34:30.500 --> 00:34:32.209
Blast it online. just
blow this whole thing up.

485
00:34:32.210 --> 00:34:33.620
It wasn't the military.

486
00:34:36.120 --> 00:34:37.919
What do you mean?

487
00:34:37.920 --> 00:34:39.919
It was me.

488
00:34:39.920 --> 00:34:40.920
I took it.

489
00:34:42.120 --> 00:34:43.380
You?

490
00:34:47.380 --> 00:34:48.919
- What the hell?
- Look. Xander.

491
00:34:48.920 --> 00:34:51.169
I thought I could figure out
what it was. you know.

492
00:34:51.170 --> 00:34:52.329
I thought it would
help Chris.

493
00:34:52.330 --> 00:34:53.959
That's bullshit!

494
00:34:53.960 --> 00:34:56.499
We should be helping each other.
not fighting each...

495
00:34:56.500 --> 00:34:57.500
Ooh!

496
00:35:00.460 --> 00:35:02.119
Come on!

497
00:35:02.120 --> 00:35:04.579
Hey! Hey. hey. hey. hey!
Get off him!

498
00:35:04.580 --> 00:35:05.959
Calvin. seriously.

499
00:35:05.960 --> 00:35:07.880
It's okay. everybody.

500
00:35:10.290 --> 00:35:11.790
I was trying to help.

501
00:35:13.620 --> 00:35:16.379
Look. if you want it.

502
00:35:16.380 --> 00:35:17.620
I'll go get it right now.

503
00:35:19.880 --> 00:35:20.960
Okay.

504
00:35:29.250 --> 00:35:30.829
We need to give it back.

505
00:35:30.830 --> 00:35:31.999
Why? What's happening?

506
00:35:32.000 --> 00:35:33.209
We don't need it anymore.

507
00:35:33.210 --> 00:35:36.249
Ryn. we need
to give it back. okay?

508
00:35:36.250 --> 00:35:37.539
No. no. no. no.

509
00:35:37.540 --> 00:35:39.249
We need to give this back.

510
00:35:39.250 --> 00:35:40.999
- Sister!
- This is not your sister.

511
00:35:41.000 --> 00:35:42.329
- Yes!
- Sister is not in here.

512
00:35:42.330 --> 00:35:44.999
We're gonna help you. Friends.

513
00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:46.619
Look. this is Xander.

514
00:35:46.620 --> 00:35:48.419
He can help
find your sister.

515
00:35:48.420 --> 00:35:50.329
but we need to give
this back to him.

516
00:35:50.330 --> 00:35:52.750
Friend. okay?

517
00:35:57.250 --> 00:35:59.619
Here. Xan. I'm sorry.

518
00:35:59.620 --> 00:36:01.669
Hey.

519
00:36:01.670 --> 00:36:05.959
I was thinking.
we should probably
work on the tracking.

520
00:36:05.960 --> 00:36:08.500
See if we can find
where the signal comes from.

521
00:36:13.120 --> 00:36:15.830
Yeah. Yeah.
okay. sure. we can try.

522
00:36:17.620 --> 00:36:18.620
What's up. Maddie?

523
00:36:18.621 --> 00:36:20.289
Hey. Xander.

524
00:36:20.290 --> 00:36:22.379
Who's this?

525
00:36:22.380 --> 00:36:25.709
Friend of mine from
the Marine Bio class
I'm taking.

526
00:36:25.710 --> 00:36:27.499
While you track that.

527
00:36:27.500 --> 00:36:30.079
I'll try to find out
more about the guy
who was on the boat.

528
00:36:30.080 --> 00:36:31.419
I can talk
to some of my colleagues

529
00:36:31.420 --> 00:36:33.289
who did some research
with the Navy.

530
00:36:33.290 --> 00:36:35.119
see if they know anything.

531
00:36:35.120 --> 00:36:37.250
We're gonna find him.
Xan.

532
00:36:46.830 --> 00:36:48.380
In the car.

533
00:37:24.620 --> 00:37:29.119
All right. Okay. so...
So we got Michael Eaton
at PRI.

534
00:37:29.120 --> 00:37:30.209
No. no.

535
00:37:30.210 --> 00:37:33.079
Maybe Amanda Cullen

536
00:37:33.080 --> 00:37:35.539
or Professor Durbin
at U-Dub.

537
00:37:35.540 --> 00:37:37.539
We could just send
a few emails out.

538
00:37:37.540 --> 00:37:39.209
nothing suspicious.

539
00:37:39.210 --> 00:37:41.209
You know. just keep it
real subtle.

540
00:37:41.210 --> 00:37:43.330
How do you subtly ask
about a mermaid?

541
00:37:46.120 --> 00:37:48.250
We got to get you
back to Helen's.

542
00:37:51.750 --> 00:37:54.460
If you find your sister.
what would you do?

543
00:37:56.540 --> 00:37:58.750
Will you go home?

544
00:38:01.960 --> 00:38:05.250
I don't think
she understands.

545
00:38:06.670 --> 00:38:09.379
Ryn. if you
find your sister...

546
00:38:09.380 --> 00:38:10.620
Yes.

547
00:39:57.040 --> 00:39:59.169
She has a quality.

548
00:39:59.170 --> 00:40:01.040
It's hard to explain.
I don't know. like...

549
00:40:03.120 --> 00:40:05.710
Like I was drawn to her.

550
00:40:09.620 --> 00:40:11.619
Me. too.

551
00:40:12.830 --> 00:40:14.329
So his neck was broken

552
00:40:14.330 --> 00:40:16.499
before he was thrown
through the window?

553
00:40:16.500 --> 00:40:17.880
Really?

554
00:40:21.290 --> 00:40:24.879
Well. you're gonna send
the report over. right?

555
00:40:24.880 --> 00:40:26.789
Non-human blood?

556
00:40:26.790 --> 00:40:31.039
What the heck
does that even mean?

557
00:40:31.040 --> 00:40:32.620
You mean like an animal
or something?

558
00:40:34.880 --> 00:40:37.830
No. Have... Have Steve drop
it off at the house. all right?

559
00:40:41.880 --> 00:40:44.749
All right.

560
00:40:44.750 --> 00:40:46.499
I'll talk to you later.

561
00:40:46.500 --> 00:40:48.749
Everything okay?

562
00:40:48.750 --> 00:40:50.209
Hey. Mads.

563
00:40:50.210 --> 00:40:51.669
Hi.

564
00:40:51.670 --> 00:40:53.620
- Ben.
- Hey.

565
00:40:54.620 --> 00:40:56.919
Yeah. Everything's fine.

566
00:40:56.920 --> 00:41:00.120
Just a. case
I'm working on.
